# Personal Expense Tracker API

A RESTful API for managing personal financial records, allowing users to record their income and expenses, retrieve past transactions, and get summaries by category or time period.

## Technologies Used

- Node.js
- Express.js
- SQLite

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd personal-expense-tracker

2. Install dependencies:
    npm install

3. Create and set up the SQLite database:
    node db.js

4. Start the server:
    node app.js

The server will run on http://localhost:3000.


## Usage
1. ## User Registration
    
    Register a new user.

    Endpoint: POST /register
    
    Body:
    
    {
    "username": "username",
    "password": "password"
    }

2. ## User Login

    Authenticate and receive a JWT token.

    Endpoint: POST /login
    
    Body:
    
    {
    "username": "username",
    "password": "password"
    }

3. ## Include the JWT token in the header for all other requests:

    Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

## API Endpoints

##User Registration

    POST /register

        Request Body:

                {
                "username": "string",
                "password": "string"
                }

        Response:

        201 Created: User registered successfully.
        500 Internal Server Error: Error message.
    
## User Login

    POST /login

        Request Body:
                {
                "username": "string",
                "password": "string"
                }

        Response:
        200 OK: Returns a JWT token.
        401 Unauthorized: Invalid username or password.

## Transaction Management
    POST /transactions

        Adds a new transaction.
    
        Request Body:

                {
                "type": "income/expense",
                "category": "string",
                "amount": "number",
                "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
                "description": "string"
                }
    
    GET /transactions

        Retrieves all transactions (supports pagination).
    
        Query Params: page, limit.

    GET /transactions/:id

        Retrieves a transaction by ID.

    PUT /transactions/:id

        Updates a transaction by ID.
    
        Request Body: Same as POST /transactions.
    
    DELETE /transactions/:id

        Deletes a transaction by ID.

## Summary
    
    GET /summary
        
        Retrieves a summary of transactions (total income, total expenses, and balance)
        
        Query Params: startDate, endDate, category.

## Reports
    
    GET /reports/monthly

    Retrieves monthly spending by category.
